.TH "scale" 9 "scale" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scale \- scale values from one range to another
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" scale
.BI "(u32 source_val "  ","
.BI "u32 source_min "  ","
.BI "u32 source_max "  ","
.BI "u32 target_min "  ","
.BI "u32 target_max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "source_val" 12
value in range [\fIsource_min\fP..\fIsource_max\fP]
.IP "source_min" 12
minimum legal value for \fIsource_val\fP
.IP "source_max" 12
maximum legal value for \fIsource_val\fP
.IP "target_min" 12
corresponding target value for \fIsource_min\fP
.IP "target_max" 12
corresponding target value for \fIsource_max\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return \fIsource_val\fP in range [\fIsource_min\fP..\fIsource_max\fP] scaled to range
[\fItarget_min\fP..\fItarget_max\fP].
